history.content:
The department recently released a policy where you can't enroll in cs 61c if you're undeclared. (Which interferes with my scheduling quite a bit - if we had a warning a semester or so in advance, I'd have taken cs 70 instead of some other techs so I could declare sooner, instead I have a new gap in my 4-year plan). 

I've heard ~30% of students drop eecs 127. Currently, it has 200/200 seats filled and 30 people waitlisted; if I waitlist during phase 1, I'll hopefully get it. cs 70 has 131/700 seats filled. The dilemma is that I don't have enough phase 1 units left (of the 13.5) to enroll in both 127 & 70. Which one should I prioritize in this situation? If I waitlist in 127 now and enroll in CS 70 for phase 2, will there still be space?
history.subject: Prioritizing CS 70 or EECS 127 Phase 1 Enrollment
